# YOLO ONNX Model Placeholder
# ================================
# This file is a placeholder for the trained YOLO model in ONNX format.
#
# To obtain a working model:
#
# Option 1: Use pre-trained YOLOv5s/YOLOv8n
#   pip install ultralytics
#   from ultralytics import YOLO
#   model = YOLO('yolov8n.pt')
#   model.export(format='onnx', imgsz=416, opset=12)
#   # Copy yolov8n.onnx to this location as best.onnx
#
# Option 2: Train custom model for Indian environment
#   - Collect dataset of local obstacles (autos, cows, potholes, etc.)
#   - Annotate using LabelImg or Roboflow
#   - Train: yolo train data=custom.yaml model=yolov8n.pt epochs=100 imgsz=416
#   - Export: yolo export model=best.pt format=onnx imgsz=416
#
# Recommended model: YOLOv8n (nano) for Raspberry Pi 4 performance
#   - Input size: 416x416 (balance of speed and accuracy)
#   - ~6M parameters, ~50ms inference on Pi 4
#
# Place the exported .onnx file here as 'best.onnx'
